gomodel:SYNGO_2773  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: Fig.1: \"NL4 associates with GlyRs\"\n- \" Thus, NL4 is localized to inhibitory, preferentially glycinergic synapses in the retina and is the only NL isoform to display such selectivity.\"\n\nFig.5: \"NL4 interacts with collybistin and gephyrin.\"\n\"We found that the intracytoplasmic domain of NL4 (NL4ICD) also interacts with gephyrin and collybistin in yeast two-hybrid assays (Fig. 5A) and GST-pulldowns (Fig. 5B). Finally, gephyrin and collybistin are coimmunoprecipitated with NL4 in chemically cross-linked extracts from mixed brainstem and spinal cord samples of WT and NL2-KO, but not of NL4-KO mice (Fig. 5D), indicating that NL4, gephyrin, and collybistin specifically associate into higher-order complexes in vivo.\"\n\n- The direct interaction of the intracellular tail of NLGN4; neuroligin-4 with gephyrin supports localization at the postsynaptic membrane (as do other known neuroligins).\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - Overexpressed NLGN4; neuroligin-4 is of mouse species: \"HA-NL2ECD/NL1ICD and HA-NL2ECD/NL4ICD constructs were created from rat and mouse NLs on the backbone of a pcDNA3 HA-NL2 construct and include the extracellular domain of rNL2 (residues 1-670), and the transmembrane and intracellular domains of mNL4 (residues 754-945) or rNL1 (residues 690-843)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2773" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

